{"text": " Okay, so this is the sound effects and music audition library. Okay, this is the sound effects and music audition library that I built. Every time you're making maybe a real or a product video, it's always good to have music sound effects where necessary to play their incidental roles and of course you have your voice over and the video itself. Now, generally speaking, it takes a bit of time to start gathering all of these elements together. So it's nice to have a library. So what I've got here is things like sound effects, stingers, risers, impacts, ambience. These are different types of effects. Okay, so for instance you've got a whooshing sound, you'll be able to audition. So there's various different ones. You've got to find what works for you. You can see that when you click play, you have the transport bar come up at the bottom of my cover, cut and copy in a little while. You can also add these to favourites, so they'll be put to a short list for you. So these are transition sounds as you scroll down, some are more cinematic, some have got longer effects that they play for longer. You just decide which ones that you want and then create a short list of those. You go through to the stingers, you're here by the way that they sound, by auditioning them. It may not play back through this because I don't have an internal loop for audio, but you will get the understanding once you have a play around and get an idea of what effects that you like. And obviously if you've got a favourites list, a lot of people tend to, if they're building out a series, have a style of sounds that they like. Okay, you don't need to overthink this part, but as you can see, transitions, you've got 58, stingers, there's 59, risers, 57. You've got impacts here, let me click this. So arrow impact, flesh impact, ground impact, really depends on what you try to achieve. Then you've got more atmospheric sounds, forest ambience, etc. And in the music, I've loaded you up with a lot of the reels that have been popular over the last few years on Instagram and of course TikTok. So there's a big collection here. And then at my, you can build out and work with your team to generate content pretty fast but keep it to a professional level. You also got a search bar here. Just be aware the search bar works on a tab level. What does that mean? Let's say I want to do Biggie Smalls, for instance. I'll type in Biggie here. You'll see there's nothing there, right? So it's going to be indexed based on the type. So if I go to music now, you've got Biggie Smalls, one more chance, press play. So now you can hear it, you can add that to your favourites here. Now in the next video, I'm going to go into the beat cutter. I've designed this so it makes your life a lot easier as Claude can do most of the work but there's certain things that you're going to need which I'll cover in the next video.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 9.0, "text": " Okay, so this is the sound effects and music audition library.", "tokens": [50364, 1033, 11, 370, 341, 307, 264, 1626, 5065, 293, 1318, 20015, 6405, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19677654389412172, "compression_ratio": 1.6933333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 0.113424152135849}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 9.0, "end": 16.0, "text": " Okay, this is the sound effects and music audition library that I built.", "tokens": [50814, 1033, 11, 341, 307, 264, 1626, 5065, 293, 1318, 20015, 6405, 300, 286, 3094, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19677654389412172, "compression_ratio": 1.6933333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 0.113424152135849}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 16.0, "end": 21.0, "text": " Every time you're making maybe a real or a product video,", "tokens": [51164, 2048, 565, 291, 434, 1455, 1310, 257, 957, 420, 257, 1674, 960, 11, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19677654389412172, "compression_ratio": 1.6933333333333334, "no_speech_prob": 0.113424152135849},